# Portal page title (`PageTitleComponent`)

Canonical top-level heading for **portal shell pages** (dashboard, table, form, placeholder). Renders an `h1` above page content on the shell background — **not** inside table/form cards.

## Component

| Item | Value |
|------|-------|
| Path | `shared/ui/page-title/page-title.component.ts` |
| Selector | `app-page-title` |
| Input | `titleKey` (required i18n key string) |
| Import | Direct path — no barrel; add to page component `imports: [PageTitleComponent]` |

```typescript
import { PageTitleComponent } from '../../../../../shared/ui/page-title/page-title.component';
```

```html
<app-page-title [titleKey]="table.titleKey" />
```

Static key (no binding): `<app-page-title titleKey="portal.admin.pages.dashboard" />`

## Where to render

**Page templates only** — first element above content (table card, form stepper, dashboard sections, etc.).

| Page type | `titleKey` source | Example |
|-----------|-------------------|---------|
| Table list (with create route) | `*.table.ts` → `table.titleKey` + `PageHeaderComponent` + `PrimaryActionLinkComponent` | See **Title-row create CTA** below |
| Table list (read-only) | `*.table.ts` → `table.titleKey` | `<app-page-title [titleKey]="table.titleKey" />` only |
| Form create/edit | `pageTitleKey` computed or `formDef.titleKey` | `<app-page-title [titleKey]="pageTitleKey()" />` |
| Dashboard / custom | `portal.<portal>.pages.*` | `<app-page-title titleKey="portal.admin.pages.dashboard" />` |
| Placeholder | route `data.titleKey` | `<app-page-title [titleKey]="titleKey" />` |

Table pages with `tableMounted` remount: place the title row **outside** the `@if` so the title stays visible during refresh.

## Title-row create CTA (table list pages with create flow)

**Required** when the feature has a list route and a create route (admin CRUD, user list + create, etc.). Compose `PageHeaderComponent` + `PageTitleComponent` + `PrimaryActionLinkComponent` — **do not** put the CTA inside `PageTitleComponent` or `DataTableComponent`.

```html
<app-page-header>
  <app-page-title [titleKey]="table.titleKey" />
  <app-primary-action-link [route]="createUrl" [labelKey]="createLabelKey" />
</app-page-header>

@if (tableMounted()) {
  <app-data-table … />
}
```

**Page component (parent owns route + label):**

```typescript
import { PageHeaderComponent } from '…/shared/ui/page-header/page-header.component';
import { PageTitleComponent } from '…/shared/ui/page-title/page-title.component';
import { PrimaryActionLinkComponent } from '…/shared/ui/primary-action-link/primary-action-link.component';
import { ADMIN_CREATE_VEHICLE_URL } from '…/shared/constants/app-urls';

protected readonly createUrl = ADMIN_CREATE_VEHICLE_URL;
protected readonly createLabelKey = 'portal.admin.nav.createVehicle';

imports: [PageHeaderComponent, PageTitleComponent, PrimaryActionLinkComponent, DataTableComponent, …],
```

- `createUrl` — create URL constant from `app-urls.ts` (never hardcode paths).
- `createLabelKey` — reuse matching `portal.<portal>.nav.create*` key when it exists.
- Place `app-page-header` **outside** `tableMounted` `@if` so title + CTA stay visible during table remount.
- Custom right-side actions: project into `app-page-header` with `pageHeaderActions` attribute instead of `app-primary-action-link`.
- **Read-only** table pages (no create route): standalone `<app-page-title>` only — no `PageHeader`.

## Do not

- Render page titles inside `DataTableComponent` or `FormPageComponent` — those frameworks handle table/form chrome only.
- Use inline `<h1 class="page-title">` or duplicate title SCSS on feature pages — styling lives in `page-title.component.scss`.
- Use `PageTitleComponent` on **guest** pages (login, register, landing) — guest pages keep their own auth/marketing title styles.
- Put create CTAs inside `PageTitleComponent` — use `PageHeaderComponent` + `PrimaryActionLinkComponent` on the page instead.
- Confuse with **form section** titles (`FormSectionComponent` / `form-section-card__title`) or **stepper step** labels — those stay in the form framework.

